name: Usha Vance
summary: Usha Chilukuri Vance is the wife of J.D. Vance, the Republican nominee for Vice President in the 2024 election. She is an Indian American lawyer and the daughter of immigrants. Usha met J.D. while attending Yale Law School, and they got married in 2014. After Trump announced J.D.'s vice presidential nomination, Usha resigned from her position at a San Francisco-based law firm. She then took to the stage to introduce her husband at the Republican National Convention, where she emphasized his personal journey. Usha's background, including her education and legal career, has been widely discussed in the media, along with her role in shaping J.D.'s views and supporting his political aspirations.

name: Russell Westbrook
summary: Russell Westbrook is reportedly set to join the Denver Nuggets after being traded from the Los Angeles Clippers to the Utah Jazz. The trade comes after the Clippers acquired Westbrook in a deal with the Lakers earlier this month. However, Westbrook is expected to be bought out by the Jazz, making him a free agent and allowing him to sign with the Nuggets. The move to Denver reunites Westbrook with Nuggets coach Michael Malone, who was an assistant coach with the Oklahoma City Thunder during Westbrook's time there. Westbrook is a nine-time All-Star and former league MVP who averaged 15.9 points, 6.2 rebounds and 7.5 assists per game for the Clippers this season.

summary: Get ready for the highly anticipated "Beetlejuice 2," as Jenna Ortega takes the spotlight in the latest trailer. Winona Ryder's involvement was contingent on a filming break if "Beetlejuice 2" occurred, and fortunately, it did. Ortega showcases her paranormal dance skills in another captivating scene. The full trailer reveals a callback dance between Catherine O'Hara and Ortega. Details about the sequel's release date, cast, and more are available in various articles. Posters and images feature the original stars alongside Ortega and Willem Dafoe. Notably, the movie's age rating differs from the 1988 original. Ryder and Tim Burton secretly met to secure the greenlight for the sequel. Fans can also catch "Beetlejuice! Beetlejuice! Beetlejuice!" at Saginaw's Lawn Chair Film Festival.

name: Biden stepping down
summary: There is growing speculation that President Biden may not seek re-election in 2024. Several prominent Democrats, including Rep. Adam Schiff, Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer, and House Speaker Nancy Pelosi, have reportedly urged Biden to step aside. They have cited concerns about his age, his low approval ratings, and the possibility that he would lose to a Republican challenger. Biden has said that he intends to run again, but he has also acknowledged that he would consider dropping out if a medical condition made it impossible for him to serve. Democrats are reportedly preparing for the possibility that Biden will not run again, and some are already considering potential replacements.
